  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "An ***expository essay*** is an essay that explains — that makes a concept, process, situation, or phenomenon clear to a reader who doesn't yet understand it. Unlike an [argumentative essay](../../../terms/argumentative-essay.md), which takes a position and defends it, an expository essay's primary obligation is to accuracy and clarity rather than to persuasion.",
